cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper proposes a novel algorithm for generalizing on related tasks by leveraging prior knowledge, which involves assigning importance weights to each past demonstration. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Robotics (cs.RO) categories. The paper also discusses the use of visual navigation, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. Additionally, the paper involves adaptation to unseen environments, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories.
